<div class="hero-unit">
  <h1>
     Node Monitor<br>
     Remote Monitoring & Control
  </h1>
</div>

<p class="message">
  <img style="float:right; margin: 0 -40px 0 20px; height: 230px; border-radius:4px" src="<%- @getUrl('/img/dashboard.png') %>">
  Node Monitor is an open source component you add to your Node.js app, and a dashboard for visualizing and controlling
  your app servers at runtime.
</p>

<p class="message">
  To add monitoring to your app servers, place the following in your initialization:
</p>
<pre style="margin: 20px 0 10px 40px; width:50%; padding: 20px;">var Monitor = require('monitor').start();</pre>
<p class="message">
  To install and run the dashboard:
</p>
<pre style="margin: 20px 0 10px 40px; width:50%; padding: 20px;">$ npm install monitor-dashboard
$ npm start monitor-dashboard</pre>

<p class="message clearfix">
  Now navigate to <a href="http://localhost:4200/">http://localhost:4200/</a> in your browser.
  The [Getting Started](<%- @getUrl('/pages/getting-started.html') %>) page has more information
  about building dashboards using the built-in components.
</p>

<p class="message">
  If you like what you see, send some &hearts; to the project team...
</p>
<pre style="margin: 20px 0 10px 40px; width:50%; padding: 20px;">$ npm star monitor monitor-dashboard</pre>

